headline: Should GoDaddy’s (GDDY) AI Identity Push Reshape Its Core Competitive Positioning Story?
summary: Earlier this week, GoDaddy launched the next phase of its Agent Name Service (ANS) with a new ANS Marketplace and curated AI agents, pairing human-readable names with cryptographically verifiable identities to help businesses discover, verify and govern trusted AI agents. The move extends GoDaddy’s long-standing domain and security infrastructure into AI identity, aiming to make agent-based workflows safer and more practical for small businesses and developers. We’ll now explore how...
